// PseudoPage
// Top-level layout and state owner for the pseudo-file viewer; manages file list, URL routing, and search overlay.
// synced: 2026-03-26T00:00:00Z

Owns global state: fileList, fileCache (Map), searchOpen, searchQuery, functions (parsed), pendingScrollTarget.
Reads current file path from the React Router wildcard param "*".
Three-column resizable layout: PseudoFileTree (left) | PseudoViewer (center, ref'd) | FunctionJumpPanel (right).
Global keyboard shortcuts: Cmd/Ctrl+K or Cmd/Ctrl+F opens search; Escape closes it.

FUNCTION PseudoPage() -> JSX.Element [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  CALLS: fetchPseudoFiles (pseudo-api), useKodexStore (kodexStore), useWebSocket (useWebSocket), useTheme (useTheme)
  Reads project from kodexStore and currentPath from URL params. On mount, calls fetchProjects and loadPseudoFiles.
  On project change, clears fileList + fileCache, navigates to /pseudo, and re-fetches files.
  Registers a window keydown listener: Cmd+K/F opens search overlay; Escape closes it.
  When pendingScrollTarget is set and functions are loaded, calls viewerRef.current.scrollToFunction then clears the target.
  Renders a fixed top header with connection status badge, refresh button, ProjectSelector, and search button.
  Below the header, renders a PanelGroup with three resizable panels: PseudoFileTree, PseudoViewer (forwarded ref), and FunctionJumpPanel. Also renders the PseudoSearch overlay (conditionally visible).

---

FUNCTION loadPseudoFiles() -> void [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: fetchPseudoFiles (pseudo-api)
  Fetches the list of pseudo file paths for the current project and sets fileList. On error, sets fileList to empty.

---

FUNCTION handleAddProject() -> void [2026-03-26]
  Prompts the user for a project path via window.prompt. POSTs to /api/projects. On success, calls fetchProjects and setSelectedProject.

---

FUNCTION handleNavigate(stem) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Navigates the router to /pseudo/<stem>.

---

FUNCTION handleSearchClose() -> void [2026-03-26]
  Sets searchOpen to false.

---

FUNCTION handleSearchNavigate(file, functionName?) -> void [2026-03-26]
  Navigates to the given file stem, closes the search overlay, and IF a functionName was provided sets pendingScrollTarget so the viewer will scroll to that function once its functions list loads.
